snippet.textDisplay:
E:U - the rap queen, absolutely killed her part with her charismatic dancing and badass & sassy lyrics, showed her charms throughout all of the song
Sihyeon - started the song off with her powerful vocals which she also showed during the bridge, killed me with her beautiful visuals
Mia - absolutely ate up her dance break, made everyone scream, shined during her part of the chorus and the 4-member mini dance break during the bridge, absolutely oozed charisma throughout the whole song
Onda - baby was so charismatic during her parts, but so beautiful and soft in her solo shots, she made me fall in love with her all over again even tough she had always been my bias
Aisha - do I even need to say anything? Iconic badass queen, killed her two rap parts, had the whole industry shaking with her power and husky voice
Yiren - made an iconic start to the song, single-handedly raised the visual standard by 3 times, killed me with her center part during the second chorus and then brought me back from the dead with her beautiful, soft vocals

Everglow - just made their 2nd comeback with their 1st mini album with a powerful title track and 3 amazing side tracks, each different from another and made the whole world look at them with them still trending in more than 20 countries (including mine) 4 days after the MV release, yet again raised to standard for rookie groups
Forevers - have made this MV the 17th kpop MV to reach the most views in 24 hours, are already halfway through to make our queens reach 100 M views on it and it's only been 4 days and will help them snatch some very much needed music show wins!

Everglow fighting! Forevers fighting! ♥️♥️♥️

snippet.textDisplay: I am going to say this now even though I feel like I'm going to get attacked lol but i believe that Yena will be joining Everglow and that her lines are taken over by Mia. Yena and Mia along with Sihyun are the strongest vocals in the group. Since their debut, you can see the significant amount of lines Mia has gotten. I also understand comments saying that the company is pushing Mia a lot, since she is very stable in singing and dancing. That doesn't mean that Mia deserves to get all this hate. There's always "justice for __ member" and I get that. But y'all need to remember this is only their 2nd comeback along with their debut song, totalling 3 promotion songs. When the other girls get enough experience in singing and dancing I'm sure they will get more lines as well. Remember, we don't know if Yena is actually joining EG but if she is, then the chances are high that some of Mia's lines are Yena's. I love this group and their songs are bops but I am not going to put down a member because I feel a sense of injustice. All members should shine, but remember this idol industry is all about marketing and not just creating groups to be famous. Much love and keep supporting! Your member will get to shine when the time comes! I hate to say it but be patient. Onda will get the love and spotlight and lines she DESERVES! 💖💕 also stream #DunDun MV!! ✌

snippet.textDisplay: It may be unfair to Onda, but music isn't about sharing the spotlight, it's about having the right amount and kind of sound at the right time, as a musician, the only rule is to create the best music possible, I don't need to think if I used the guitar the same amount of times as the keyboards, that's stupid. Every moment, no matter how long or short, is there for the right and best reasons. So Onda's parts is important as well if it is there no matter how short it is. Our only hope is to find a song that would showcase the voice that we like cuz it fits the sound. EU for example can't rap much on songs that doesn't have one. will you force a rap part if it would be unnecessary to a song? Second, as a producer, I don't want to be bound by a rule, or a condition, I make the sound that I want, and give it to someone who I find would satisfy the outcome that I needed in the song. Again it may be unfair on idol's standpoint. But we can't have everything at once. I'll pray next time we find a good song for all of them. For me, music wise, "player" is the best song for me, followed by "salute".
